    <title>How to Make Grilled Cheese</title>
   </head>

   <body>
    <section>
        <h1>Mmm, mmm, good!</h1>
        <figure>
            <blockquote>
                <p>Image of an awesome grilled cheese sandwich.
                </p>
            </blockquote>
            <blockquote>
                <figcaption>
                    
                    <cite>
                        <a href="https://natashaskitchen.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Grilled-Cheese-Sandwich-SQ.jpg">
                        </a>
                    </cite>
                </figcaption>
            </blockquote>
        </figure>
     </section>

     <section>
        <h2>Ingredients you'll need:</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            - 2 pieces of bread
                        </li>
                        <li> 
                            - 2 pats of butter
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            - 1 slice of monterey jack cheese
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            - 1 slice of aged cheddar cheese
                        </li>
                    </ul>
     </section>

     <section>
        <h3>Process:</h3>
               <ol>
                  <li>
                    1. Fetch yourself a fat-bottom skillet
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    2. Heat the skillet over medium heat
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    3. Butter one side of each slice of bread
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    4. Place one slice of the buttered bread, buttered side down, into the skillet
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    5. Quickly place each slice of cheese on the bread, being sure to cover the entire surface area
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    6. Place the other slice of bread, butter side up, on top of the cheese
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    7. Wait approximately 1 to 2 minutes (or till the bread touching the skillet is a golden brown)
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    8. Flip the sandwich over with some awesome pizazz and cook the other side till golden brown (approximately 1 to 2 minutes)
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    9. Eat with ketchup, or just enjoy the plain crispy goodness of your grilled cheese
                  </li>
                </ol>
        <p>
            <strong>Note:</strong>Grilled cheese is great on a grill, but for a quicker method, try using a clamshell panini press. The result will be much quicker, allowing you to make many more for you and your friends.
        </p>

        <p>
            Remember, Shaun says "Grilled cheese sandwiches are a staple of the North American diet!".
        </p>
    </section>
    
